    "John Trapp": "Ver. 14. {See Trapp on \"Mt 10:2\"} {See Trapp on \"Mt 10:3\"} {See Trapp on \"Mt 10:4\"} {See Trapp on \"Mr 3:14\"} {See Trapp on \"Mr 6:7\"}\nVer. 14. {See Trapp on \"Mt 10:2\"} {See Trapp on \"Mt 10:3\"} {See Trapp on \"Mt 10:4\"} {See Trapp on \"Mr 3:14\"} {See Trapp on \"Mr 6:7\"}\n14. Ver.\n14. This is of a truth that prophet ] Yet anon they are at it, \"What sign showest thou?\" that you may know them to be the Pharisees\u2019 disciples. Of whose sour leaven also that in the next verse savours; where they would needs take him by force to make him a king, #Joh 6:15 . They could not imagine a Messiah that had not an earthly kingdom.\nVer."
